{"key":"post-6626387","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6626387</id>\n<content>The taller the better, because you'll have more cubic inches of space inside.  You don't want a small chamber that gets CO2 saturated.  A tiny chamber will need to get fanned out much more often.  If you drill a bunch of holes for air exchange, it can be hard to keep humidity up in a small chamber.  I'd consider about 14&quot; to 16&quot; the minimum height.  You'll need room in the bottom for your damp perlite.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6626712</next>\n<prev>6626158</prev>\n<first>6625867</first>\n<last>6626712</last>\n<when>1172813671</when>\n<utime>03/02/07 07:34 AM</utime>\n</post>"}